{{Infobox organization | name = esSENSE Club | native_name = എസ്സൻസ് ക്ലബ് | native_name_lang = ML motto = Promote Science and Free-thought | image = https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/ | image_size = | alt = | caption = | logo = | logo_size = 150px | logo_alt = essense club kerala india | logo_caption = esSEBSE club logo | formation = 01June 2016 | founding_location = [[Thrissur]], Kerala, India | registration_id = TSR/TC/541/2016 | main_organ = Executive committee and Members General Body organization | type = [[Non-governmental organization|NGO]] | status = Registered under The Travancore-Cochin Literary, Scientific and Charitable Societies Registration Act, 1955 | purpose = Promote Science and [[Humanism]] and work as per Article 51A(h) of [[constitution of India]] | headquarters = [[Kochi]], [[Kerala]], [[India]] | location = [[Kochi]], [[Kerala]], [[India]] | region = Worldwide | membership = <200 | membership_year = 1 to 10 | volunteers = >2500 | volunteers_year = 2018 | slogan = esSENSE - We seek truth, science, and rationality as the essence of life | website = [https://www.essense.club|esSENSE.club] | Publication = esSENSE Freethinkers Diary | leader_title = President | leader_name =Aravind K | leader_title2 = Secretary | leader_name2 = Mohammed Ashraf }}
'''esSENSE Club''' is a club promoting [[atheism]], science and [[humanism]] based in [[Kerala]], [[India]]. Founded in 2016, the club emphasises propagating [[freethinking]] and [[rationalism]] among the [[Malayali]] community all over the world. esSENSE Club organises seminars, lectures and debates on most weeks of the year on topics related to atheism, science and politics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://essense.club/about-essense/ |title=Mission of Essense}}</ref> The club jointly organised a debate series named ''Samvadam'' along with [[Times of India]] and Inspirit IAS Academy at Thiruvanthapuram in April 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/thiruvananthapuram/toi-samvada-from-today/articleshow/58016836.cms |title=esSENSE- Times of India Debate Series 2017 }}</ref> The annual fest of esSense named Essentia was conducted in October 2017 at Town Hall, [[Ernakulam]]. Malayalam author and rationalist C. Ravichandran was a regular speaker for esSense till an organisational split took place in 2018. Apart from having units in all the districts of Kerala, esSense also has units in [[Bangalore]], [[Melbourne]], [[Sydney]], [[Perth]] in Australia, United Kingdom and United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://europe.manoramaonline.com/uk/2017/11/08/essence-britain.html |title=esSENSE UK Formation }}</ref>
According to its website, "esSENSE aspires to be the premier rationalist platform in India. We bring together rationalist speakers, writers, thinkers, activists, supporters, and well-wishers, with the goal of promoting rationalism and freethinking in Kerala and in the larger global environment. Through our publications, e-magazines, seminars, online media, and other collaborative platforms, we will endeavor to develop rationalist thought, share ideas, expand our intellectual horizons, facilitate learning, and foster collaboration. We build a better tomorrow that embraces science and rationality, pursues freethinking and atheism, and elevates humanism and justice, while resisting superstition, quackery, ignorance and hatred."
==Split== [[File:Ravichandran C.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Ravichandran]] esSENSE Club suffered a vertical split when a section of the office-bearers questioned attempt to create a personality cult around C Ravichandran, at whose behest the organisation was set up. This faction alleged that Ravichandran is fostering a fan club around his personality while the opposing faction charged the former with financial misappropriation. Police cases were filed and are pending resolution.
